@* Provides the element Blazor's circuit-reconnect machinery binds to
   (via id="components-reconnect-modal"). When this element is in the
   DOM the framework toggles the components-reconnect-{show, retrying,
   paused, failed, rejected, hide} class on it instead of injecting its
   own default overlay/dialog tree. The button uses an inline DOM
   event because the SignalR runtime is gone in this state — a Blazor
   @onclick handler can't fire. *@

<div id="components-reconnect-modal" class="reconnect-modal">
    <div class="reconnect-card">
        <div class="reconnect-spinner" aria-hidden="true">
            <div></div>
            <div></div>
        </div>
        <p class="reconnect-msg reconnect-msg-show">
            Reconnecting to the server… attempt
            <span id="components-reconnect-current-attempt">1</span>
            of
            <span id="components-reconnect-max-retries">8</span>.
        </p>
        <p class="reconnect-msg reconnect-msg-paused">Connection paused.</p>
        <p class="reconnect-msg reconnect-msg-failed">Reconnection failed.</p>
        <p class="reconnect-msg reconnect-msg-rejected">Could not reconnect to the server.</p>
        <button type="button" class="reconnect-reload" onclick="location.reload()">Reload</button>
    </div>
</div>
